==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tuberculin test
<hw>Tu*ber"cu*lin test</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>The hypodermic injection
of tuberculin, used as a test for past or present infection with
tuberculosis. It is used both for humans and cattle.</def> <note>In
humans, a previous or acive infection with tuberculosis will cause a
distinct reaction to the injection of tuberculin. The test is thus used
to screen populations to discover those who may harbor an active
tuberculosis infection, and more definitive tests are performed on those
showing a positive reaction, to determine if the infection is active. In
cattle there is little or no effect of the injection of tuberculin on
healthy animals, but there is a marked rise in temperature in
tuberculous animals.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tuberculization</ent>⟦br⟧
